@node Main "Xess - Documentation"

                               'Xess'  1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Xess' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} where you have to place 32 coloured
'X' shapes on an 8 by 8 tile board. Place 'X' shapes so that part
of an 'X' shape is placed on one tile and the other part is on a
tile that is at the upper right, lower right, lower left or upper
left, next to the first tile, 'bridging' both tiles.

  'X' shapes can 'cross' each other, as long as both are of a
different colour. Also, any 'X' shape can be rotated, if there is
at least one other empty tile where that 'X' shape can pivot to...

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

