@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Xess' where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

  Gameplay is quite simple: just click on any empty tile. If no
other 'X' shapes are interfering, meaning that there are no part of
an 'X' shape located at the upper right, lower right, lower left
and upper left tile next to the clicked tile, a coloured 'X' shape
will be placed there, bridging both tiles.

  There are 32 'X' shapes to be placed, and that number is
subdivided in 4 groups of 8 'X' shapes that are in each of 4
available colours taken from the Workbench screen colour palette.
So, place each coloured 'X' shape wisely so that you don't make
extra unnecessary moves...

  One thing that complicates the game a little, is that you do not
know in advance the colour of the next 'X' shape. If that 'X' shape
cannot be placed because it crosses another shape of the same
colour and/or it is at the edge of the game board, a little 'X'
will appear on the clicked tile, with the colour of the next
potential 'X' shape... wasting a move in the process.

  Any 'X' shape can be rotated from one connecting tile to another,
if another connecting tile is already occupied by an 'X' shape, the
clicked 'X' shape will rotate clockwise and connect to the next
empty tile (if there is at least one) located diagonally to the
clicked tile.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

